⚙️ Remove Eddy_NG

Connect via SSH and run: 

cd ~/eddy-ng && ./install.sh --uninstall && cd ~/klipper && git pull

But if you experience problems with updating Klipper via git commands, you can manually clear out eddy-ng changes directly with:

cd ~/klipper && git restore src/Makefile klippy/extras/bed_mesh.py

⚙️ Step-by-Step: BTT Eddy USB Setup & Calibration for Sovol SV08 (Mainline Klipper)

1. Connect via SSH and ensure you’re on Mainline Klipper:cd ~/klipper && git checkout master
2. With kiauh update all (min version v0.13.0-641)
3. Install katapult in BTT Eddy (https://github.com/Rappetor/katapult-on-btt-eddy)
4. Change mcu serial in /options/probe/eddy_tap.cfg (use ls /dev/serial/by-id/* in 10)

Save and restart


🔌 Drive Current Calibration

5. Move manual the toolhead to 20mm above the bed. If you plan to use it as an endstop, move the gantry manually to this position.
6. Run the calibration command in your Klipper terminal:

LDC_CALIBRATE_DRIVE_CURRENT CHIP=btt_eddy 

Result typical value 14 to 16

SAVE_CONFIG

📏 Mapping Eddy Readings to Nozzle Heights

7. Edit saved_variables.cfg

Change show_freq = '' to show_freq = '1'

Save and restart

8. This macro include G28 X Y and SET_KINEMATIC_POSITION Z=346

Run in web GUI console:

PROBE_EDDY_CURRENT_CALIBRATE_AUTO CHIP=btt_eddy

9. Follow the Klipper UI prompt:Lower the nozzle until it grips a piece of paper placed on the bed (classic paper test method). The paper should slide with some resistance.

Result:

probe_eddy_current: noise 0.000875mm, MAD_Hz=15.350 in 4038 queries

10. Accept the prompt and let Eddy map height readings.When finished, run:

SAVE_CONFIG

